			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Lida Brau on the establishment of two ghettos in Hlyboke, one for the younger and one for the older Jews, executions,
					liquidation actions, Jewish self-defense, and transports to Lublin. After the loss of her family, she run away to the nearby
					forests, where she joined a Soviet partisan unit. She describes the battle near the township Vileika.</p>
			</abstract>
