	<text>
		<body>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_01.jpg"/></p>
			<p>Archive of the Jewish Historical Institute</p>
			<p>Testimony of <persName ref="#ehri_et_braun_lida">Braun Lida</persName></p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">Daughter</term> of <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_braun_dawid">Dawid</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_braun_cyrla">Cyrla</persName>, née <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_braun_cyrla">Fiszer</persName>, born in <date when="1933">1933</date> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Glubokoye</placeName>, <placeName ref="#ehri_et_wilno_voivodeship">voivodeship
					of Vilnius</placeName>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">Education</term>: three
				years of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-842" type="subject">primary school</term>. Until <date
					when="1942">1942</date>, she lived with her <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>parents</term>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> was a tailor.
				During the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-632" type="subject">occupation</term> she lost her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">parents</term>, two <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brothers</term> and a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sister</term>.</p>
			<p>When the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> came to our town in <date when="1941">1941</date>, we lived at
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Bialystok street number 48</placeName>. On the third day the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_belarusians">Belarusians</term> incited the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				and they took away all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothing</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">cooking</term> utensils from our home.</p>
			<p>A few thousand Jews lived in our town. When the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> came, more than a thousand
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> with the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russian army</orgName>.</p>
			<p>After a few days, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_geler"
					>Geler</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bodov">Bodov</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kozliner">Kozliner</persName> and some
				others, about 16 persons, brought them to a hill behind town called <q><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html"
						>Piaskovatke</placeName></q> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term>
				them. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_belarusians">Belarusians</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">buried</term> them.</p>
			<p>Jews had to bring all the goods from their shops to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> authorities and traded
				in the marketplace. But the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_belarusians">Belarussians</term>, not willing to have Jews in the
				marketplace, incited the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> and Jews <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">were forbidden to trade in the marketplace</term>. At
				the same time the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">ordered that Jews had to give away gold and
					furs</term>.</p>
			<p>After a certain time, Jews were moved into the following streets: <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Vilner</placeName>, a half of <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Drujer</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Kishleker</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Dobrove</placeName>, and told that Jews only had
				right to move in the territory of these streets. They carried white <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-338"
					type="subject">bands</term> on their arms, but the life was not so bad, the trade did not stop.</p>
			<p>A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-579" type="subject">Judenrat</term> was created. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_lederman">Lederman</persName>, a former fabric dealer, was appointed as the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject">chairman</term>. The militia consisted of former
				traders: <persName ref="#ehri_et_libe_toybes_ike">Ike Libe-Toybes</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_blant_yude">Yude
					Blant</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_gordon_khaym_ber">Khaym-Ber Gordon</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_vaynshteyn_ayzik"
					>Ayzik Vaynshteyn</persName> and others.</p>
			<p><pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_02.jpg"/></p>
			<p>All Jews had to go to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> for the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554"
					type="subject">chairman</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_lederman">Lederman</persName> would speak to people and warn them to be obedient, not to go to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">forbidden areas</term> and not to try to avoid <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>.</p>
			<p>When the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> demanded money and gold and Jews were not in hurry to bring it to
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-579" type="subject">Judenrat</term>, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject">chairman</term> with the militia went to look for it
				in people’s homes.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> would force the people to go to
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. If one of them was angry at
				someone, he would give that person in <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> hands and the
				person would not come back.</p>
			<p>Once the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policemen</term> came to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject">chairman</term> and explained that there were too many
				Jews, some of them had to be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>. The
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject">chairman</term> pleaded that there were young
				people, good workers, who were useful to the authorities and they would continue to be very useful. And they answered that if there
				were strong ones and weak ones, two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghettos</term>
				would be established, one for the young who would <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
					>work</term> and one for the old and weak who would be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532"
					type="subject">shot</term> in stages. The second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject"
					>ghetto</term> was in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Kisholeyk
					street</placeName>.</p>
			<p>The Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> menaced every Jew with
				moving them to the second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. When the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">demanded gold, a contribution</term>, and a Jew
				could not pay this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">tax</term>, they would send him
				to the second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>.</p>
			<p>Around a thousand people lived in the second <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject"
					>ghetto</term>, the old and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term>, as
				well as between twenty and thirty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term>
				that did not have any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1053" type="subject">gold to give away</term>.</p>
			<p>Two days later the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName> came to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-579" type="subject">Judenrat</term> and demanded 700 persons to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shoot</term>. As the second <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> had been established, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject">chairman</term> told them to go to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Kisholeyk</placeName>.</p>
			<p>On the same day, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> surrounded
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Kisholeykes</placeName> and took people
				out of their homes. A part of them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term>
				themselves and stayed inside, because the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject"
					>police</term> did not search too diligently.</p>
			<p>On the following day at dawn I saw the people from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197"
					type="ghetto">Kisholeyki</placeName> marching one next to the other, with a hand on the other’s shoulder. They were led to the
				forest</p>
			<p><pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_03.jpg"/></p>
			<p>called <q><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Borok</placeName></q> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> there.</p>
			<p>Two months later, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> ordered all the
				Jews to assembly in one square (the horse market) and started to verify the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> cards. On some of them, they wrote
					<q>master [?]</q> and from that we immediately understood that those who had such cards would live. The remaining ones received
				cards with coded names: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/624079/orsha.html">Orsha</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/630376/barysaw.html">Borisov</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/491687/smolensk.html">Smolensk</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Those with the master [?] card immediately returned home. The remaining ones figured out that <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/630376/barysaw.html">Borisov</placeName> meant <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Borok</placeName>. This is the forest where the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killings</term> take place. Indeed, after a few hours
				these people were taken to the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Borok</placeName> forest and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> by the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term>.</p>
			<p>From then on, every evening, during the return from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
					>work</term>, <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> would grab one Jew and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shoot</term> him.</p>
			<p>After half a year of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>’s existence,
				when the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisans</term> attacked the neighbouring
				towns <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/629002/dokshytsy.html">Dokshitsy</placeName> and <placeName ref="#ehri_et_krulieuscyna"
					>Krulevshtshina</placeName>, with which lots of <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term><note place="bottom"
					>Sentence unclear in the original, some words must be missing.</note>, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
					>Germans</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto">Glubokoye</placeName>
				became fearful the same would not happen in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-197" type="ghetto"
					>Glubokoye</placeName>, and their order the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-554" type="subject"
					>vice-chairman</term> of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-579" type="subject">Judenrat</term>,
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_blond_yudl">Yudl Blond</persName>, to assemble all the Jews in order to be brought to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>.</p>
			<p>In the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>, it suddenly became very silent,
				no one showed up in the street. After a few hours, as if they had concerted, a few <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> with small bundles appeared in the
				street; as the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> were still nowhere to be
				seen, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> opened fire in the direction of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. No one answered them any shots, so they
				entered the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term>. Just as they appeared in
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> streets, heavy fire met them.
				Grenades were thrown at them. Many of them <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject"
					>fell</term> from the first shots. I saw three <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> lying <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>. But the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> started to shoot at every house and
				threw a grenade in every window. The Jews realized that the situation was hopeless, so everyone took their bottle of petrol and set
				the house, where they were, on fire. In the smoke and fire, people ran</p>
			<p><pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_04.jpg"/></p>
			<p>where they could.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> also set houses on fire. The fire flames illuminated the whole town.</p>
			<p>When the shooting started, my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> went out
				into the street to look what was happening and was hit with a bullet in the neck. I, my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">sister</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> went out, moved the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> away from the street and went up to the
				attic. Because of the suffocating smoke, my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>father</term> went down. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>
				could not walk and fell down from the attic. I went down, helped the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term> to her feet and started to run to my
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>.</p>
			<p>From below, I heard shouting:</p>
			<p>– Halt!</p>
			<p>I looked around and did not see my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term>. We
				lied down on our bellies. A <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> approached and shot at my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mother</term>. I saw him loading his gun, so I stood
				up and ran away. After a second, I managed to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject"
					>hide</term> myself under a brick house. It was the evening already, the smoke was irritating the eyes, I could not see where I
				was going. Wandering around the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> like
				that, I felt that someone was following me and I tried to pronounce my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term>’s name. Indeed, he answered. Then we
				both walked through the ruins. People were running, we followed them. The machine guns were still shooting. During a short distance we
				had to fall on our bellies a few times.</p>
			<p>When the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> fence had burned down, I and
				my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> left the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-545" type="subject">ghetto</term> territory. We entered a garden and slept
				there until the dawn.</p>
			<p>When the day came, my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">brother</term> told me to go
				have a look where the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> where. I left the garden. Two <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> were standing looking at the other direction. I could not go back, so I went
				through the fields and the forests to the villages and asked, where the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisans</term> where.</p>
			<p><pb n="5" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_05.jpg"/></p>
			<p>During the fire, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> told us that if
				someone from us stayed alive, they should go the village called <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/624103/orekhovno.html"
					>Arebova</placeName><note place="bottom">Orekhovno</note>, 5 kilometers from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Glubokoye</placeName>. I spent a whole day wandering in the woods until I came
				to that village.</p>
			<p>I called my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">father</term> by name, but no one
				answered. However, peasants that knew my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject"
					>father</term> and heard me shouting, warned me I should quickly go away because the village elder was coming. I ran fast down the
				hill and entered a forest. Walking, a heard a pig squeak. Following the sound of the squeaks, I found myself on a path, where I met
				peasants from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Glubokoye</placeName> I knew; I followed their horse
				cart.</p>
			<p>I saw <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> on the road, so I quickly <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ran away</term> and entered a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cemetery</term>. I saw that they were following me and
				they caught me. They asked me who I was. I answered that I was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763"
					type="subject">Christian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girl</term>. They laughed and told me not to be
				afraid, that they knew I was a Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girl</term>.
				They asked me where I was going.</p>
			<p>– I’m following my nose, I answered.</p>
			<p>– Tell me, do you want to go to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject"
				>partisans</term>? – one of them asked again.</p>
			<p>– I don’t know, I don’t have where to sleep – I answered.</p>
			<p>– Go to this house, you’ll be able to sleep there – one of them said and pointed where to go.</p>
			<p>I entered the house and asked for something to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
					>drink</term>. I received it. The owner of the house questioned me who I was, I answered that I was form <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Glubokoye</placeName>, but he did not allow me to sleep at his place. He told
				me to go away immediately.</p>
			<p>Leaving a house, I saw a non-Jew ploughing. I approached him and asked if I could sleep at his place. He answered no, but called me
				back and gave me instructions to enter a barn where I could sleep. He brought me <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> in the morning. Then he came back again
				soon and told me:</p>
			<p>– Two Jews have just passed by, run quickly!</p>
			<p><pb n="6" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_06.jpg"/></p>
			<p>I ran and shouted to the Jews to wait, but they did not stop. I continued to run and caught up with them. They were people from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/627908/hlybokaye.html">Glubokoye</placeName> I knew, a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-741" type="subject">married</term> couple. I went to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisan</term> area with them. They left me in a
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-763" type="subject">Christian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term>’s house and left. I asked how to reach
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisan</term> units. I was not accepted into
				three units. Young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">guys</term> sat with guns. They
				questioned me who I was, from where I came and told me to go to another village 1,5 kilometer away from that village.</p>
			<p>Going there I asked a peasant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> where the
				commander was. At the moment, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> was
				passing by on a bicycle and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> told me
				to ask him.</p>
			<p>I stopped him, showed him the note from the commander of the previous village which said we should contact the regional commander.</p>
			<p>He immediately led me to a house in the village. I waited in the street. He was the commander of the 5th unit, from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/524901/moscow.html">Moscow</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov
					Vania</persName>.</p>
			<p>I met Jews I knew there. The commander asked them if they knew me, they answered negatively, but I knew them.</p>
			<p>I entered the house. After having a rest, I went to the kitchen and helped to peel the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term> and with other chores.</p>
			<p>After two weeks, all the nine units went to attack <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/620181/vilyeyka.html"
				>Vileyka</placeName>.</p>
			<p>I learnt that <persName ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_rodionov"
					>Rodionov</persName> had been taken <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject"
					>prisoners</term> by the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>. When the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> were shooting the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians">Russian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners</term>, <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_rodionov">Rodionov</persName> proposed the
					<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> to create a brigade to fight against the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisans</term>. The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> gave them a permission, and they organized quite a large group, armed with
				shotguns and machine guns. <persName ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_rodionov"
					>Rodionov</persName> went over to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject"
					>partisans</term> and created the nine units.</p>
			<p>I was 5 kilometers from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/620181/vilyeyka.html">Vileyka</placeName> and I was told that during
				the attack <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/620181/vilyeyka.html">Vileyka</placeName> had been burned down. People ran away,
				lots of <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> were taken as <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners</term>. From the midday, the fight</p>
			<p><pb n="7" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010025_07.jpg"/></p>
			<p>continued until the following morning.</p>
			<p>Two Jewish young <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> from our 5th unit,
					<persName ref="#ehri_et_bik_leybl">Bik Leybl</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/623042/prazaroki.html"
					>Prozoroki</placeName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_krivitski_ziomke">Ziomke Krivitski</persName>, were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term>, they were burned during the fire.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov</persName> also <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">fell</term>.</p>
			<p>Afterwards, we returned to the woods. <persName ref="#ehri_et_druboshovski">Druboshovski</persName> took over <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_konstantinov_vania">Konstantinov</persName>’s place. <persName ref="#ehri_et_rodionov">Rodionov</persName> decided
				to reach the front. Just as they had crossed the railway, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> surrounded
				them. We were 15 persons to stay. We waited the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> to come looking for us, but
				they did not come. I learned that <persName ref="#ehri_et_rodionov">Rodionov</persName> had also been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> and that the brigade was scattered. Our
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hideout</term> was also discovered, 15 persons
				were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term>. I ran away and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hid</term> myself.</p>
